adjectives.description: sensable (comparative more sensable, superlative most sensable)

entries.meaning: Capable of being sensed; perceptible, tangible.
examples: Although his mind remained aware that he was physically seated within a sensable booth, all his senses told him that he was experiencing the story that was happening around him.
Put on your thinking cap and go see an intellegent[sic], intensly[sic] well thought out noir/science fiction film with a plot that makes sensable, practical use of phenominal[sic] special effects.
